[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man 'stable' after being struck by a car in Portadown

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man is in a stable condition after being struck by a car in Portadown, County Armagh.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The incident happened on Market Street on Saturday.
The Northern Ireland Ambulance Service said the man was taken to the Royal Victoria Hospital in Belfast after suffering a head injury.
The police have said that diversions are in place and advised motorists to avoid the town centre.
